---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { href } from "../lib/url";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — Irrevon"
  description="Irrevon's local-first data boundary, identifier handling, telemetry, fixtures, and operator responsibilities."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <span class="kicker">Privacy</span>
      <h1>Local-first does not mean data-free.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The CLI has no telemetry, update checks, crash reporting, or hosted Irrevon service. Runtime
        records stay in the operator's PostgreSQL deployment. The static project site may use
        same-origin Vercel Web Analytics and Speed Insights when deployed.
      </p>
      <h2>Workbench boundary</h2>
      <p>
        <code>irrevon serve</code> binds only to <code>127.0.0.1</code>, validates the Host header,
        accepts GET/HEAD only, and connects through a SELECT-only database role. Stable upstream
        identifier keys remain visible, while values are represented as deterministic SHA-256
        digests. Raw values require the explicit local CLI <code>inspect --reveal</code> option.
      </p>
      <h2>What the ledger stores</h2>
      <p>
        The ledger stores intent metadata, request parameters needed for recovery, digests,
        transitions, receipts, probes, and findings. Request parameters can contain personal or
        confidential data when an integrator puts it there. Digests are not anonymization, especially
        for low-entropy values.
      </p>
      <h2>Operator responsibilities</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimize provider payloads and keep credentials outside configuration files.</li>
        <li>Set retention, backup, access-control, and deletion policy for the deployment.</li>
        <li>Treat evidence exports, screenshots, logs, and backups as potentially sensitive.</li>
        <li>Never submit production records, keys, or private identifiers to public issues.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Security reports use the private path on the <a href={href("/security/")}>Security page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
